Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"AA\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>Epidoc editing and addition of metadata\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"ZL\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0009-0007-0586-7956\">Zoé Lienard\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>named entity annotation\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic003988\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\">334476\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003988\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-23\">10.5281/zenodo.4389521\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative\n                        Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\n                    \u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Lipari\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/048\">Museo Archeologico Regionale Eoliano \"Luigi Bernabò Brea\"\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">11632\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                    \u003Csupport>\n                                        \u003Cp>Large stele with poorly polished surfaces, rougher on the back; missing corner on the left\u003C/p>\n                                        \u003Cp>The slab bears two distinct inscriptions on the front, relating to two different phases of use: the first (a) placed in the upper part, the second (b) on a projecting band at the base of the same face. Here is the text of (a)\u003C/p>\n                                        \u003Cp>The surface of the upper part of the front face shows clear traces of gradine work and seems to have been lowered with respect to the original surface, probably to erase an older text and to engrave the inscription (a). This could therefore be attributed to the reused of the slab as a funerary stele. The inscription (b) should instead belong to a first use of the stone; the position at the lower end of the forehead leads us to believe that the slab was originally not a stele – in which case the base would have been buried – but a slab covering an unidentifiable struture (funerary monument? enclosure?)\u003C/p>\n                                        \u003Cp>On same support as \u003Cref sameAs=\"ISic004283\">ISic004283\u003C/ref>\u003C/p>\n                                        \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.volcanic\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/28.html\">volcanic (pietra di Fuardo)\u003C/material>\n                                        \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.stele\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250\">stele\u003C/objectType>\n                                        \u003Cdimensions>\n                                            \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">108\u003C/height>\n                                            \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">42.5\u003C/width>\n                                            \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">14\u003C/depth>\n                                        \u003C/dimensions>\n                                    \u003C/support>\n                                    \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.damaged\"/>\n                                \u003C/supportDesc>\n                                \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                    \u003Clayout>\n                                        \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                        \u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.complete\"/>\n                                    \u003C/layout>\n                                \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003C!--ILipara-->\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"35\" atMost=\"70\">35-70\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462283\">Lipara\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2524378\">Lipari\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.48333, 14.93333\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1971\">Discovered in 1971 during the excavation of trench XXXI, face O (Bishop's property). It was reused in masonry tomb no. 1225 (dated to the 2nd century CE)\u003Cgeo>38.467130, 14.953871\u003C/geo>\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- representative geo for contrada Diana -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/